parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The power steering seizes when making turns at slow speeds
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is unable to stay aligned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end shimmy or wobble can cause loss of control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes violently
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is unable to stay aligned

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module solenoid can cause the key to fall out of the ignition while the vehicle is in motion, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The key falls out of the ignition while the vehicle is in motion
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is unable to stay aligned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive line can cause loss of control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The support bearing on the drive shaft fails
the vehicle is unable to stay aligned
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to shut off without warning, resulting in loss of power, lights, and assisted braking, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off without warning
the key is hard to turn
the vehicle shuts off when hitting a bump
the vehicle has intermittent power loss.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear actuator can cause the switch from heat to air conditioning to be inoperable, resulting in discomfort and inconvenience for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The switch from heat to air conditioning is inoperable

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to the driver and passengers.
Fuel spillage during fueling can cause a fire hazard, damage to the vehicle's paint and components, and environmental contamination.
symptoms: Fuel spills out of the spout when the tank is full

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high pressure fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and power brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when towing a trailer.
